header.gameNote: PARADISE JAM AT ST THOMAS VI

article.headline: Drexel 68, Winthrop 45
article.story: ST. THOMAS, U.S. Virgin Islands -- Frantz Massenat scored 23 points and Samme Givens added 12 points and seven rebounds to lead Drexel past Winthrop 68-45 in the seventh-place game of the Paradise Jam. Massenat was 6 of 8 from behind the arc for Drexel (2-2). The Dragons, who had lost to Norfolk State and Virginia in its first two games of the tournament, shot 48 percent from the field, including 11 for 21 from 3-point range. Drexel opened the game strongly, with Massenat making a 3-pointer, Givens scoring on a hook shot and Damion Lee hitting a 3 to help the team to a 14-1 lead. The Dragons led by as many as 17 in the first half and took a 31-22 lead into the break. Andre Jones led Winthrop (0-5) with 18 points.
